cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.SP, cs.MA, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis of the sensitivity of estimation mean-square error to the level of phase synchronization mismatch in coherent MIMO radar systems. This involves the study of the lower bound on the MSE, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the analysis of a distributed radar system, which involves the study of system dynamics, control, and optimization. 
3. cs.SP (Signal Processing) - The paper deals with the analysis of coherent MIMO radar systems, which involves the study of signal processing techniques for radar applications. 
4. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper deals with the analysis of a distributed radar system, which can be viewed as a multi-agent system. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the analysis of a distributed radar system, which involves the study of networking and communication protocols for radar applications.
